> I have noticed that the motherboard voltage supplied to
> AMD K6 cpu by FIC motherboards is sometimes too low. Try
> upping the voltage a notch or two and see if that fixes
> it. It did for us on several K6 systems which were
> experiencing random corruption / sig11.
There is an acknowledged issue with the PS on the FIC
boards. It's especially noticeable with 2MB of cache and a
fast K6-3, since that sucks quite a bit of power. Tom's
Hardware has a little bit of info under one of his most
recent video card reviews, for those who are interested.
